<TITLE> Police arrest knifeman Ashraf after 3 days </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 31 (bdnews24com)  The police have arrested Ashraf Ali from Kaliganj, three days after he stabbed his girlfriend and her parents in an altercation over money. Officer in charge of Kaliganj police chief Abdul Awal confirmed the news to bdnews24.com late Tuesday. He said, "We've come to know that Ashraf was arrested from one of his relative's house." "We've heard that the DB police arrested him from Dhanpur. His relative was also arrested." On Mar 27morning, Ashraf stabbed his girlfriend Barsha, and her parents at their Kalabagan residence where he had stayed overnight. Kalabagan police station's sub-inspector, Tariqul Islam, had said, "Barsha and Ashraf appeared to have become involved at university." But Ashraf had demanded Tk 20 lakh from Barsha's father and upon being refused became violent. Tariqul said Ashraf fled the scene in the morning after stabbing the three persons. Ashraf's uncle Mujibur Rahman, said his family had no idea that Ashraf was in fact living in Bangladesh. "He had gone to England for studies last year." Tariqul, the investigation officer, told bdnews24.com on Tuesday that Ashraf was in the custody of detective branch. On Mar 24 in the Gulshan's Kalachandpur area, a businessman and his wife were shot dead by a man who allegedly wanted to marry their daughter. bdn
